divs: Sighting DetailsI was sitting on the beach and put my sunglasses on, and looked up at the sun. Immediately, I noticed a circular, dim, shadowy sphere - about the same size as the sun, from that distance - moving through the clouds Northeast. I looked around and also saw several airplanes and birds, but none were that high and none looked spherical in nature. I caught the attention of my friend and tried to get her to see what I was seeing, but she couldn't find what I was looking at. I followed it through the clouds - for about 30 seconds - and just when the clouds broke and the object should have appeared, it simply was just not visible any longer. I was incredibly intrigued and excited, as it was definitely one of those moments that is truly perplexing. I knew I was seeing something that I've never seen before.
Summary: Dim, shadowy circle moving through clouds.
